DataElement.preferredDefinition: A piece of glass or plastic on which different samples have been affixed at separate locations in an ordered manner thus forming a microscopic array.  The samples are usually DNA fragments but may also be antibodies, other proteins, or tissues.:The state of being complete or undivided, of being sound or undamaged.:An essential and distinguishing attribute of something or someone; a degree or grade of excellence or worth.:A number or range of numeric values measuring performance, function, quality, or ability._The state of being complete or undivided, of being sound or undamaged.:A numerical quantity measured or assigned or computed._Generic value domain for a primitive java datatype that is a Double-precision floating point number (64-bit IEEE 7540).
